    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-13T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1599: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-13T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 13, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 13—7:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 10, 1 p.m., to Nanking. Formal proposal has been received. My
                    British colleague recommended to his Government favorable consideration in
                    principle.</p>
                <p>I believe we should not object but we must of course bear in mind that the
                    Chinese may never resume payments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
